(function(){const pages=[{"idx":0,"href":"/docs/about/","title":"about","content":" Huddersfield Creative Coding This site is a place to aggregate a variety of creative coding projects from artists, hackers and coders living in the Greater Huddersfield area.\nThe views and resources on this page are not affiliated with the University of Huddersfield.\n"},{"idx":1,"href":"/docs/projects/","title":"code/projects","content":" code/projects A number of creative projects, libraries and codebases have emerged from the members of the CCL. This page acts as a resource to document and archive those projects. JuliaCollider\nFrancesco Cameli FrameLib\nAlex Harker HISSTools Library\nAlex Harker \u0026amp; Pierre-Alexandre Tremblay iPlug2\nOli Larkin and Alex Harker AHarker Externals SOURCE\nAlex Harker  HISSTools Impulse Response Toolbox\nAlex Harker \u0026amp; Pierre-Alexandre Tremblay M4l Convolution Reverb Externals\nAlex Harker Wayverb\nReuben Thomas Siren\nCan Ince Audileum\nCan Ince \u0026amp; Others   "},{"idx":2,"href":"/docs/people/","title":"people","content":" people The people listed here are either residents of or significant contributors to the creative coding scene in Huddersfield.\nAlex Harker  Alex is a Senior Lecturer working at the Huddersfield of University. He is a creative coder, composer and hardcore DSP programmer. Francesco Cameli  Francesco is a coder, composer specialising in C\u0026#43;\u0026#43;, SuperCollider and live coding. He currently is studying his Masters at the University.  Frederic Dufeu \n\nOli Larkin  Oli is an independent audio software developer since 2003. He is a major developer for iPlug2, and has contributed significantly to the Web Audio API. He is considered a specialist in audio development internationally, and his VirtualCZ project has reached critical acclaim among composers, performers and gear-heads alike.  Jacob Hart  Jacob Hart is a musicologist, musician and PhD student at the University of Huddersfield. He makes tools in Max, Python and Javascript that help musicologists analyse sound through technological mediums.   "},{"idx":3,"href":"/docs/contact/","title":"contact","content":" contact This page is run by James Bradbury.\nAll communication should be directed toward jamesbradbury93(at)gmail.com\nYou are also welcome to submit pull requests at the source code.\n"},{"idx":4,"href":"/categories/","title":"Categories","content":""},{"idx":5,"href":"/docs/","title":"Docs","content":""},{"idx":6,"href":"/","title":"home","content":" news and coding events "},{"idx":7,"href":"/tags/","title":"Tags","content":""}];window.bookSearch={pages:pages,idx:lunr(function(){this.ref("idx");this.field("title");this.field("content");pages.forEach(this.add,this);}),}})();